   "source": [

    "# Model Evaluation API Examples\n",

    "\n",

    "This demonstrates how to use the [evaluate_model](../../docs/python_api/operations.md#evaluate_model) API.\n",

    "\n",

    "Refer to the [Model Evaluation](../../docs/guides/model_evaluation.md) guide for more details.\n",

    "\n",

    "__NOTES:__  \n",

    "- Click here: [![Open In Colab](https://colab.research.google.com/assets/colab-badge.svg)](https://colab.research.google.com/github/siliconlabs/mltk/blob/master/mltk/examples/evaluate_model.ipynb) to run this example interactively in your browser  \n",

    "- Refer to the [Notebook Examples Guide](../../docs/guides/notebook_examples_guide.md) for how to run this example locally in VSCode  "

   ]

  },

  {

   "cell_type": "markdown",

   "metadata": {},

   "source": [

    "## Install MLTK Python Package"

   ]

  },

  {

   "cell_type": "code",

   "execution_count": 3,

   "metadata": {},

   "outputs": [],

   "source": [

    "# Install the MLTK Python package (if necessary)\n",

    "!pip install --upgrade silabs-mltk"

   ]

  },

  {

   "cell_type": "markdown",

   "metadata": {},

   "source": [

    "## Import Python Packages"

   ]

  },

  {

   "cell_type": "code",

   "execution_count": 1,

   "metadata": {},

   "outputs": [],

   "source": [

    "# Import the necessary MLTK APIs\n",

    "from mltk.core import evaluate_model"

   ]

  },

  {

   "cell_type": "markdown",

   "metadata": {},

   "source": [

    "## Example 1: Evaluate Classification .h5 Model\n",

    "\n",

    "The following example evaluates the [image_example1](https://github.com/siliconlabs/mltk/blob/master/mltk/models/examples/image_example1.py) model \n",

    "using the `.h5` (i.e. non-quantized, float32 weights) model file.  \n",

    "This is a \"classification\" model, i.e. given an input, the model predicts to which\n",

    "\"class\" the input belongs.\n",

    "\n",

    "The [model archive](../../docs/guides/model_archive.md) is updated with the evaluation results.  \n",

    "Additionally, the `show` option displays interactive diagrams."

   ]

  },

  {

   "cell_type": "code",

   "execution_count": 2,

   "metadata": {},

   "source": [

    "# Evaluate the .h5 image_example1 model and display the results\n",

  {

   "cell_type": "markdown",

   "metadata": {},

   "source": [

    "## Example 3: Evaluate Auto-Encoder .h5 Model\n",

    "\n",

    "The following example evaluates the [anomaly_detection](https://github.com/siliconlabs/mltk/blob/master/mltk/models/tinyml/anomaly_detection.py) model \n",

    "using the `.h5` (i.e. non-quantized, float32 weights) model file.  \n",

    "This is an \"auto-encoder\" model, i.e. given an input, the model attempts to reconstruct\n",

    "the same input. The worse the reconstruction, the further the input is from what the \n",

    "model was trained against, this indicates that an anomaly may be detected.\n",

    "\n",

    "The [model archive](../../docs/guides/model_archive.md) is updated with the evaluation results.  \n",

    "Additionally, the `show` option displays interactive diagrams and the `dump`\n",

    "option dumps a comparison image between the input and reconstructed image."

   ]

  },
